         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Honoured Doctor, ¶  ¶ Would you be so kind as to enclose the present little communication of Dr Hooker's in your next consignment to Dr F. von Mueller? ¶  The same will perceive from it that the way h...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.12.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">[W. Sonder] to H. Nördlinger</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">This letter is on the back of this part of a letter by J. Hooker to H. Nördlinger forwarded to M.</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: end; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Kew</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: end; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Jay 14/1869</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I regret much that I cannot comply with your request with regard to the Australian woods indicated, which are not of the nature you suppose. They consist of immense polished slabs, which are all mounted on stages, &amp; to remove these, &amp; cut sections from them, would take many weeks of labor, involve a great expense &amp; seriously disfigure the whole collection. Of many of the specimens the weight is so great that two men cannot lift them. Nor do </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> consist of pieces of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">young wood</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> (branches), all are slabs, polished, to show the nature of the grain for art</seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">?</seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> purposes. If you could come here you would I am sure at once see the impracticability of sending you pieces of these specimens.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am quite aware of your beautiful publication <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the woods (published by F.G. Cotta) a copy of which we possess.</seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">?</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Regretting much that I cannot accede to your request</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very faithfully Yr</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Prof Nordlinger</p>
               </note>Honoured Doctor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you be so kind as to enclose the present little communication of Dr Hooker's in your next consignment to Dr F. von Mueller?<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hooker's letter, written on the back of the MS, was forwarded to M:</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: end; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Kew</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: end; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Jay 14/1869</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I regret much that I cannot comply with your request with regard to the Australian woods indicated, which are not of the nature you suppose. They consist of immense polished slabs, which are all mounted on stages, &amp; to remove these, &amp; cut sections from them, would take many weeks of labor, involve a great expense &amp; seriously disfigure the whole collection. Of many of the specimens the weight is so great that two men cannot lift them. Nor do </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> consist of pieces of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">young wood</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> (branches), all are slabs, polished, to show the nature of the grain for art purposes. If you could come here you would I am sure at once see the impracticability of sending you pieces of these specimens.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am quite aware of your beautiful publication <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the woods (published by F.G. Cotta) a copy of which we possess.</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Regretting much that I cannot accede to your request</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very faithfully Yr</p>
                  <p rend="valediction"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 2.2429in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Prof Nordlinger</p>
                  <p rend="letter"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">i.e. </seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; font-style: italic; ">Querschnitte von Holzarten</seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 9pt; ">, 11 vols, Stuttgart 1856-88, 1100 plates [ie sections of wood] in boxes. A set of this publication is in the Library at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Melbourne.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note> The same will perceive from it that the way he recommends to me in 'brevi manu' to obtain possession of new timbers has miscarried. I believe to have added to the earlier writing already that the sound wood of young trunks (principally of these), yet also old ones, is suitable for cross sectioning and that pieces of 15 cm. fibre lengths to a large number of slices — ? — .</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wishing at all times to oblige both Dr Mueller and yourself.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your devoted</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Commissioner-of-woods Nördlinger</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
